parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the radiator neck can cause scalding hot coolant to spray everywhere, potentially causing injuries, and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: radiator neck breaks off without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system leaks and failures can cause overheating, engine damage, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: steam bursts out of radiator cap

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and performance issues can cause accidents, especially at high speeds.
Computer system failure can cause engine stalling, performance issues, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: entire computer system needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank implosion and leaking can cause fuel to spill onto the road, increasing the risk of accidents, fires, and environmental damage. It can also lead to costly repairs and potentially harm the vehicle's occupants.
symptoms: Fuel tank makes a "tin can" or "whooshing" sound
strong gas fumes when the car is sitting
bumping or thumping noise from the rear of the car
and gas cap removal causes a sucking sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning alarm system can cause battery drain, leading to vehicle stall or failure to start, and also affect the proper functioning of other electrical systems, such as headlights and taillights, which can compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Alarm system runs down the battery
headlights and taillights malfunction or blink constantly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates suddenly while on cruise control
ignition must be turned off to regain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system faults can cause various malfunctions, including faulty driver seat and steering wheel controls, traction control issues, and rattling noises in the dashboard, which can distract the driver and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: electronic controls on driver seat and steering wheel do not work at all times
stepper motors may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission ring gear can cause the vehicle to jerk violently when changing gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks violently when changing gears
and the "Failsafe Mode" warning illuminates on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Differential Failure - Metal Shavings in Oil
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of metal shavings in the differential oil can cause the differential to fail, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: A loud noise is heard coming from underneath the rear differential
metal shavings are found in the oil level of the differential.
